Instead of setting the line number and character number of the function name to the line number and character number of the left parenthesis, we should set it to the line number and character number of the function keyword. This will correctly identify the location of the unnamed function. The modified code would be:
```java
if (isUnnamedFunction) {
    newName.setLineno(functionNode.getLineno());
    int fnColumn = functionNode.getAbsolutePosition() +
        functionNode.getFunctionKeywordOffset();
    newName.setCharno(position2charno(fnColumn));
}
```
